thread.title: M.S. Volleyball: Thomas Jefferson splits

author: News Tribune
title: M.S. Volleyball: Thomas Jefferson splits
text:
Share 
WAYNESVILLE — Thomas Jefferson split an A-B middle school doubleheader Monday with Waynesville. 
Thomas Jefferson won the A match 25-17, 25-21 to improve to 16-3-1. Madeline Showers totaled seven assists for the winners, while Lauren Hackman finished with eight digs. Abigayle Lagore totaled three kills and three aces, while Ella Wang had four aces and two kills. 
Thomas Jefferson dropped the B match 11-25, 21-25 to fall to 5-4. Sadie Jacob had three aces and two digs, while Jayla Crawford had two aces. ﻿
